Here's a PlantUML sequence diagram representing the control flow of the IBM Cognos Analytics system based on the provided repository summary:

```plantuml
@startuml IBM_cognos-analytics-to-visualize-business-data

actor User
participant "Node.js Scripts" as NodeJS
participant "CSV Files" as CSV
database "Data Warehouse\n(Db2 or Netezza)" as DW
participant "IBM Cognos Analytics" as Cognos

User -> NodeJS: Run data generation scripts
activate NodeJS

NodeJS -> NodeJS: Generate sample business data
NodeJS -> CSV: Write data to CSV files
activate CSV

NodeJS -> DW: Load data into warehouse
activate DW
CSV --> DW: Data ingestion
deactivate CSV

User -> Cognos: Connect to data warehouse
activate Cognos

Cognos -> DW: Establish connection
DW --> Cognos: Connection established

User -> Cognos: Create data modules
Cognos -> DW: Query data
DW --> Cognos: Return data

User -> Cognos: Build dashboards and visualizations
Cognos -> Cognos: Process and visualize data

User -> Cognos: Analyze data
Cognos --> User: Display interactive visualizations

deactivate NodeJS
deactivate DW
deactivate Cognos

@enduml
```